The ratification process required 36 states, and completed with the approval by Tennessee. Though not necessary for adoption, the following states subsequently ratified the amendment. Some states did not call a legislative session to hold a vote until later, others rejected it when it was proposed and then reversed their decisions years later, with the last taking place in 1984.<ref name=":8" /><ref>{{cite book|title=Women of the American South: A Multicultural Reader|editor=Farnham, Christie Anne|chapter=Black Women's Culture of Resistance and the Right to Vote|last1=Hine|first1=Darlene Clark|last2=Farnham|first2=Christie Anne|pages=[https://archive.org/details/womenofamericans0000unse/page/204 204–219]|publisher=NYU Press|location=New York|date=1997|isbn=9780814726549|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/womenofamericans0000unse/page/204}}</ref>
